```js
async function classifySessionFenceChange(params) {
  const allowAnyMessage = params.expectedPublishedEntries !== void 0;
  return (params.expectedPublishedEntries ? await classifyOwnedSessionFileInitialization({...}) : void 0) 
    ?? await classifySessionFenceAdvance({...}) 
    ?? await classifySessionFenceRewrite({...});
}
```

When `expectedPublishedEntries` is set, it calls `classifyOwnedSessionFileInitialization` first. Let me look at that:

```js
async function classifyOwnedSessionFileInitialization(params) {
  if (!params.current.exists || params.previous?.fingerprint.exists === true && params.previous.fingerprint.size > 0n || params.current.size > MAX_SAFE_FILE_OFFSET) return;
  ...
}
```

This requires `previous.fingerprint.exists !== true` (i.e., file didn't exist before) OR `previous.fingerprint.size === 0n`. My test 4 had `previous = readSnapshot(file)` where the file didn't exist, so `previous.fingerprint.exists` is `false`. So that should work.

But wait — my test 4's `classifyChange` doesn't have this `classifyOwnedSessionFileInitialization` path. It only has the "advance" path. Let me add it to my test:

